parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Power Transfer Unit (PTU) can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the "Service 4WD" warning light illuminates
the vehicle fails to respond to accelerator pedal input
the vehicle stalls
and the transmission grinds or makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the rear differential housing cracks or leaks fluid
the vehicle makes unusual noises
and the vehicle's performance is affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the transmission grinds or makes unusual noises
and the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause the engine to fail, leading to a loss of power, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the engine
the "Check Engine" warning light illuminates
and the engine performance is affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto start-stop system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
especially when coming to a stop; the engine goes silent and then fails to restart; the car loses power and takes a moment to regain power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery and electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving; the battery warning light illuminates; the vehicle is unable to start; the electrical system malfunctions
causing issues with the radio
thermostat
and camera.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the parking/emergency brake can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The parking/emergency brake engages unexpectedly; the vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving; the parking/emergency brake warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The radio switches channels randomly; the touchscreen display malfunctions; the GPS system changes randomly; the seat and radio settings change on their own.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Key Fob and Ignition System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the key fob and ignition system can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The key fob fails to unlock the vehicle; the ignition system fails to start the vehicle; the PUSH to START button fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine wiring harness can cause a fire, leading to a risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The engine wiring harness catches fire; the wires show heat damage and bare wires are exposed.
